    "Junming et al. (2021) conducted harvesting trials on apples using an impact vibratory picking machine, which achieved an efficiency of more than 90% but caused damage to the plant.",
    "Zhang et al. (2015) designed a comb-and-brush berry picking machine to harvest mature fruits with a picking rate of 86.70% and a fruit damage rate of 8.62%, pointing out that comb-and-brush harvesting can cause different degrees of damage to branches and leaves.",
    "The push-shear harvesting technique caused less damage to fruits, but the net harvesting rate was lower (Yu and Ampazidis 2022).",
    "Shear harvesting may cause damage to the fruits as the stalks are not cut at a good distance, which tends to destroy the fruits (Xu et al. 2023).",
    "Although the use of orchard harvesting machinery has become widespread, damage to fruits and stems during harvesting still occurs, which constrains the development of this equipment."
